The next morning - about ten and a half hours later - after a rocking journey that produced the old world cadences in the famous documentary The Night Mail, I arrived in the Turkish capital - a new city, designed to rule a new secular state, far from the Ottoman past.
However, the AKP, with its clear Islamist roots, represents a paradigm shift in the Turkish consensus.
which has aroused some suspicion in the West and especially in Washington.
